<SPAN class=intro_copy>See Your Ingenuity In a Whole New Light</SPAN>
<P><STRONG>Accepting Submissions: August 27-September 28, 2007</STRONG><BR>They're the fruits of your labors, so go ahead and show them off at this annual competition honoring outstanding consumer electronics design and engineering. Your products could win a coveted spot at the 2008 International CES and "oohs" and "aahs" from thousands of attendees and members of the press.</P>
<P>Innovations 2008 Design and Engineering Award honorees will be featured at the Innovations Plus in the Sands Expo and Convention Center. A short shuttle ride from the Las Vegas Convention Center places you at the doorstep of the Sands, home of the yearâ€™s honorees recognized for outstanding consumer electronics design and engineering.</P>
<P><STRONG>Tips for Preparing an Innovations 2008 Entry Online</STRONG> </P>
<UL>
<LI>You'll be required to create a user account to submit an entry. Even if you had a user account last year, a new account is required. </LI>
<LI>Remember your username/password, as you may wish to edit an entry or submit additional entries later. </LI>
<LI>Eligible Innovations 2008 products must be available to U.S. consumers through retail or your company's website no earlier than March 1, 2007, and no later than February 29, 2008. </LI>
<LI>Download the <A href="/print/docs/2k8_Innovations_Rules.pdf" target=_blank>Rules and Eligibility Guide</A> and the <A href="/print/docs/2K8InnovationsCategoryGuide_web.pdf" target=_blank>Product Category Guide</A> (.pdf). </LI>
<LI>Use Notepad or Wordpad to type in the required information. </LI>
<LI>Focus on providing substantive information, not creative formatting, or typefaces. Entries will be given a standardized look before judges see them. </LI>
<LI>Cut, paste, or retype the information into the online entry tool. </LI></UL>
